p. 127. Peter sancte omnipotens deus. This prayer is not found in the earliest Sacramentaries‚ and is absent from Egb., but appears in Lan, D., and T. lt maintains its place in the later English Pontificals but does not seem to have been usual elsewhere. Menard appears to have found it only in books of English origin and in the Codex lietoldi, which seems to have been influenced by English sources. But it appears also in the non-English part oi the Leofric Missal, where it precedes Deus honorum omnium and has the title oi consecratio. Possibly its original source may be the same which supplied the Gelasian additions to the Leonine forms ior the Ordination of Priests and Deacons.
